# clang-format configuration for the sound module.
# Based on Google with the handful of overrides we already rely on:
#   * 100-column lines (matches the bulk of existing code).
#   * 4-space indentation (consistent with the majority of touched files).
#   * Never sort includes automatically — several files rely on platform
#     headers coming after the module's own (e.g. `<spawn.h>` after
#     `<cstdio>` in `PiperSpeech.cpp`).
#   * Keep pointer-alignment left (`T* x`, not `T *x`) to match the codebase.
BasedOnStyle: Google
IndentWidth: 4
ColumnLimit: 100
AccessModifierOffset: -4
PointerAlignment: Left
DerivePointerAlignment: false
SortIncludes: CaseSensitive
SortUsingDeclarations: true
AlignAfterOpenBracket: Align
AllowShortFunctionsOnASingleLine: Inline
AllowShortIfStatementsOnASingleLine: WithoutElse
AllowShortLambdasOnASingleLine: All
BreakBeforeBraces: Attach
BreakConstructorInitializers: BeforeColon
SpaceAfterCStyleCast: true
FixNamespaceComments: true
---
Language: Cpp
Standard: c++17
